dmca.title: Russian Language Author Claims Copyright Infringement
dmca.body:
Attn: [private]
Fax: [private] (9 pages)    
From: [private]    

Dear Goggle [sic] team,    
Before I start the formal listing of the infringement of copyright texts, please, 
let me shortly describe the problem.    The texts -- my books and articles -- are 
displayed at the moment on two web sites: one is my legal and official web site that 
is olegarin.com and another - rusglobus.net, where my works are placed without my 
permission. I have applied many times to rusglobus team to remove my pages from 
rusglobus.net, but they have refused my request. I would like to stress that 
rusgloblus.net does not have my written permission and signature to keep my works 
on their web site.    All my works are signed as Oleg Arin (that is my Russian 
pseudonym) and as Alex Battler (my legal name). That is why I ask the Google team 
to remove my pages under both of my names from rusglobus.net, listed on Google 
search engines.    The works at issue are the texts that infringed my copyrights 
and are not the copyright of rusglobus.net appeared on Google.com, Google.ca, 
Google.ru which I wanted to be removed are as follows:
